{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T16:00:13.012Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Test Coverage — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Test Coverage"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a metric that measures the quantity and quality of testing performed—specifically, what is tested and how much code, platforms, and user scenarios are checked. It answers: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "\"How much of my code/requirements have been validated by tests?\""}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test coverage includes gathering information about which parts of a program are actually executed when running the test suite, determining which branches of conditional statements have been taken. In simple terms, it's a technique to ensure your tests are testing your code—or how much of your code you exercised by running the test."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key distinction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Test coverage vs. Code coverage:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Test coverage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Overall test plan—what requirements/functionalities are tested\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Code coverage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Specific code lines executed when application runs"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It Matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Without measuring test coverage:\n- Untested code paths slip into production with hidden bugs\n- Critical requirements go unverified\n- You can't identify gaps in testing\n- Defects leak to users after release\n- wasted resources on redundant or meaningless tests"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test coverage helps "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "track software test quality"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "cover unvalidated areas"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "avoid problems and catastrophes"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". It prevents defect leakage and determines all decision points and paths in your application."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Impact"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Identifies untested code"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Shows which areas need additional test cases"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Improves quality"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assures test quality and indirectly measures product quality"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevents defect leakage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Catches bugs before release, reducing post-release defects"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Eliminates redundancy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Helps identify and remove useless/redundant test cases"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Controls scope"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keeps time, scope, and cost under control"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Early defect prevention"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prevents defects at early project lifecycle stages"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ROI improvement"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prevents wasting resources eliminating defects after release"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limitation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Consequence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "100% ≠ 100% tested"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High coverage doesn't guarantee all bugs found"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Can encourage waste"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Teams may add meaningless tests just to boost %"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "False confidence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High coverage can mask poor test quality"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Maintenance cost"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "More tests = more maintenance overhead"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not comprehensive"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Doesn't test logic quality, just execution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Time investment"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Achieving high coverage requires significant effort"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test Coverage Formula"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "To calculate test coverage:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Count total lines of code in the software component\n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 2"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Count lines executed across all existing test cases"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "Formula:\n\\[\n\\text{Test Coverage \\%} = \\left(\\frac{\\text{Lines Executed}}{\\text{Total Lines}}\\right) \\times 100\n\\]"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\nIf a system component has 500 lines of code and test cases execute 50 lines:\n\\[\n\\text{Coverage} = \\left("}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "Example:\nIf a system component has 500 lines of code and test cases execute 50 lines:\n\\[\n\\text{Coverage} = \\left(\\frac{50}{500}\\right) \\times 100 = 10\\%\n\\]"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test Coverage Example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If you have:\n- 15 requirements\n- 150 tests created\n- 120 tests executed"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "**Test coverage** = \\( \\frac{120}{150} \\times 100 = 80\\% \\) [testfort](https://testfort.com/blog/what-is-test-coverage-in-software-testing)"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test Coverage Types"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Product Coverage"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tests software from a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "product perspective"}, {"type": "text", "text": "—checking performance across wide scenarios, not just functionality."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Focus"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": How the product might be utilized in real-world extremes."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How to improve"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Prioritize requirements\n- Prepare checklists\n- Implement effective test automation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Requirements Coverage"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Assesses if required features exist and function properly."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Focus"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Meeting user requirements—product is useless if it can't meet them."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Risk Coverage"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Meticulously tests all software-related risks and problems."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prioritization strategy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High impact + High probability"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Test first (mandatory)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low probability + High impact"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Test (critical scenarios)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High probability + Low impact"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Test if time/resources available\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low probability + Low impact"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Can skip"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. Compatibility Coverage"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tests across devices, operating systems, browsers, and hardware configurations."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scope"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- 9,000+ devices, 21 OS, 8 browsers\n- Android + iOS platforms\n- Network conditions: Wi-Fi, 3G, 4G"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. Boundary Value Coverage"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tests boundaries and values immediately below/above."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\nFor minimum input value of 1, test:\n- 0 (below boundary)\n- 1 (boundary)\n- 2 (above boundary)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Minimizes \"off-by-one\" bugs."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "6. Code Coverage (Subtype)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Measures how much source code is tested."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Types"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Line coverage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Percentage of lines executed\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Branch coverage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Percentage of branches taken\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Function coverage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Percentage of functions called\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Class coverage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Percentage of classes instantiated"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to Achieve Test Coverage"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Method"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Works"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Static review"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Peer reviews, inspections, walkthroughs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ad-hoc to automated"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transform ad-hoc defects into executable test cases"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Automated code coverage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Automated tools at code/unit test level"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Functional test coverage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test management tools for functional coverage"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AI-aided automation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Self-improving test sets using machine learning"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Test Coverage Metrics"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Metrics help measure and monitor testing activities, answering:\n- Is testing against right platforms/environments?\n- How much was tested?\n- How long to properly test?\n- How many problems failed to spot?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Top metrics"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n1. Percentage of test execution coverage\n2. Faults per platform\n3. Requirements coverage\n4. Number of test cases by requirement\n5. Defects spotted per requirement\n6. Bugs found per functional area\n7. Test case performance in finding defects"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Beyond devices/platforms, consider "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "user conditions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Phone call interruptions\n- Memory consumption\n- Network switching\n- Background processes\n- Low battery"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Ideal Coverage Levels"}]}, 